<br>
Ok Skald changes with this patch look good but I still think there is a little left to go to get the class back where it needs to be.  Small but simple things<br>
<br>
1)        Give Skalds either a smaller set of Resist songs or give them the equivalent of the Advanced Resistance Chant Paladins receive.  As they are configured right now they are of little use. <br>
2)        Up one of the DDs in Range (I would suggest the Level 44) to 1250.  Skalds have no function in keep defense.  This is only going to get worse with the new keep design.  Upping the range to 1250 on one shout is going to have very little effect in open field RvR.<br>
3)        Improve the Skald Defense.  Even with the improved HP skalds still have woeful defense and little ways of improving it.  Add Evade 2 or 1.75 spec points so that parry can be brought up to usable levels. Or Better yet, Both.<br>
4)        Second Combat Chant.  A second in combat chant has long been a request of the skald communities.  Since Skalds cannot twist this would not overpower the class just give options.  The best thing I think would be to change the Song of Rest into a skald specific in combat chant.  Up it so that it regens about 50 hp a pulse plus a level 2/3 end regen.  This would not overshadow other Midgard classes and would give Skalds option to use in combat.<br>
5)        FIX Fury of the Gods, so that it is a useful 14-point group RA.  The skill is the right idea but woefully lacking in effect.  It needs to be a 15 to 20 dps RA for 30 seconds every 15 min.<br>
<br>
With this I would be very happy for a long time with my class.<br>
